---
import SectionLabel from './ui/SectionLabel.astro';
import AnimatedCounter from './react/AnimatedCounter';
---

<section class="bg-void py-section-mobile md:py-section animate-on-scroll">
  <div class="max-w-narrow mx-auto px-6">

    <SectionLabel text="The Problem" />

    <h2 class="font-sans font-bold text-heading-mobile md:text-heading text-off-white mb-8">
      You plan the week perfectly. Then the week happens.
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-5 font-sans text-lg text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Monday morning. Fresh start. You write down your three strategic priorities for the week.
        The ones that actually move the needle — the hiring plan, the process overhaul, the partner proposal.
      </p>
      <p>
        By Wednesday, none of them happened. Your calendar was hijacked by three 'urgent' requests
        that turned out to be someone else's poor planning. You spent two hours in a meeting that
        could have been an email.
      </p>
      <p>
        You've read the books. Atomic Habits, Deep Work, The 7 Habits. You know the theory better
        than most. But theory doesn't block your calendar. Theory doesn't send you a message at 5pm
        asking: <span class="text-off-white italic">what did you actually do today?</span>
      </p>
      <p>
        The gap between what you know and what you do is the most expensive gap in your career.
        Not because you're lazy. Because you don't have a system that makes execution unavoidable.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Cost anchor -->
    <div class="mt-12 p-8 rounded-xl bg-void-card border border-void-border relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber/5 to-transparent pointer-events-none"></div>
      <div class="relative">
        <p class="font-sans text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-amber mb-4">The cost of inaction</p>
        <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2 mb-4">
          <span class="text-amber font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl">€</span>
          <AnimatedCounter target={50000} suffix="+" className="text-amber font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl" client:visible />
          <span class="text-text-muted text-lg">/year</span>
        </div>
        <p class="font-sans text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
          The knowing-doing gap costs you <strong class="text-off-white">€50,000+ per year</strong> in unrealized
          revenue — and that's before counting the promotions, relationships, and self-trust you're
          leaving on the table. You've already spent more than €997 on this problem in the last 90
          days. You just didn't write a check for it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
